other_tests.procedure_name: CT Abdomen and Pelvis with Contrast
other_tests.findings: Appendix is dilated, measuring up to 10 mm, with mural hyperenhancement, periappendiceal fat stranding and adjacent fascial thickening, consistent with acute uncomplicated appendicitis. No free intraperitoneal air, periappendiceal abscess or free pelvic fluid or other finding to suggest macroperforation. Other abdominal organs (liver, pancreas, spleen, kidneys) demonstrate normal findings.
